node.title: Carlton's Liam Jones announces AFL retirement after reportedly refusing COVID-19 vaccination
node.alt: A Carlton AFL player holds the ball in two hands during a 2021 premiership match.
node.description: The Blues confirmed Jones's retirement effective immediately, with the defender saying it is for "personal reasons".
node.content: ["Carlton's Liam Jones has announced his retirement from the AFL after reportedly refusing to receive the COVID-19 vaccination.", "The Blues released a media statement on Sunday afternoon confirming Jones's retirement, without referencing his vaccination status.", "Jones said he made the decision for \"personal reasons\".", "\"I wish to announce my retirement from AFL football effective immediately,\" Jones said in the statement.", "\"I want to take this opportunity to thank all who have supported me throughout my journey, both personally and professionally. I love the game and I'll miss my teammates.", "\"I hope that people respect my decision and privacy \u2014\u00a0neither myself or my management team will be making any further comment on the matter.\"", "More to come."]
